<ul>
	<li><span class="MovieTitle" onmouseover="showPic('pic101', 'blue')" onmouseout="hidePic('pic101')">101 Dalmatians</span>, Peter Pan, Lady and the Tramp, and Mulan are among the only animated Disney films where both parents are present and don&#39;t die during the course of the movie.</li>
	<li>A hyena biologist sued Disney for portraying hyenas as villains in <span class="MovieTitle" onmouseover="showPic('picLion', 'yellow')" onmouseout="hidePic('picLion')">The Lion King.</span></li>
	<li>Christian Bale voiced the character of Thomas in Pocahontas.</li>
	<li>The group Abba was originally intended to do the music for The Lion King, but they weren&#39;t available, so Disney went with Elton John.</li>
	<li>Frozen is the first animated Disney film directed by a woman.</li>
	<li>Finding Nemo harmed clownfish populations after people started buying tons of pet clownfish after seeing the movie.</li>
	<li>Andy didn&#39;t have a dad in Toy Story because human characters were expensive and difficult to animate.</li>
	<li>It would take about 9.4 million balloons to lift Carl&#39;s house in Up.</li>
	<li>Beauty and the Beast was the first ever animated film to be nominated for an Oscar for Best Film.</li>
	<li>Pride Rock and the Gorge in The Lion King are modeled after Hell&#39;s Gate National Park in Kenya.</li>
	<li>Tangled&#39;s Rapunzel and Flynn Rider make an appearance at Elsa&#39;s coronation in Frozen.</li>
	<li>During the Snow White production, Walt Disney kept a menagerie of animals on the studio lot as live reference for the animators.</li>
	<li>Walt Disney was presented with an honorary Oscar for Snow White and the Seven Dwarfs, presented in one normal-sized statuette and seven miniature Oscars.</li>
	<li>Snow White and the Seven Dwarfs was the first film to ever release a motion-picture soundtrack.</li>
	<li>John Lennon turned down Walt Disney Studios&#39; request for the Beatles to provide the voices of the vultures in The Jungle Book.</li>

</ul>
